ABUJA (SundiataPost) – Nigeria on Tuesday appeared to have entered a dangerous level in COVID-19 infections as the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) reported 663 new cases of COVID-19, the highest daily record of new infections.Lagos, which is the epicentre of the Coronavirus pandemic in Nigeria reported 170 new cases; closely followed by Ogun State with 108 cases.Bauchi and Ebonyi got 69 and 49 respectively while Edo and Rivers reported 33 and 30 respectively. The total number of confirmed cases in Nigeria now stand at 13,464. The full report is as follows: Deaths increased to 365. Lagos-170Ogun-108Bauchi-69Ebonyi-49Edo-33Rivers-30FCT-26Jigawa-26Delta-20Anambra-17Gombe-16Kano-16Imo-15Abia-14Borno-11Oyo-11Plateau-8Kebbi-6Kaduna-6Ondo-4Niger-2Katsina-2Osun-1Ekiti-1Kwara-1Nasarawa-1 13464 cases of #COVID19NigeriaDischarged: 4206Deaths: 365 A breakdown of cases by state is as follows: By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) -  Nigeria Monday announced 229 new confirmed cases of COVID-19 with  seven deaths while the total number of patients discharged so far stand at 2,311, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has reported. The NCDC which released the report on its official twitter handle  informed… May 26, 2020 In "Top Stories" …Says No New State Reported a Case in the Last 24Hours By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) on Tuesday recorded 276 new cases of the COVID-19, adding that no new state reported a case in the last 24 hours. The Nigeria Centre… May 27, 2020 In "Top Stories" ABUJA (SundiataPost) - There is a sudden rise in COVID-19 cases in Edo and Rivers states, according to figures released Monday night by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control ((NCDC). Bothe states reported 41 and 33 cases respectively. They are part of the 416 new cases reported by NCDC. This… June 2, 2020 In "Top Stories"